description:
&lt;p&gt;Aspen is a 24 bed functional later life ward, covering Bristol and South Glos service users. The ward is currently operating as a treatment ward in line with the COVID-19 ward configuration.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a highly motivated and enthusiastic Band 5 Staff Nurse to join our experienced and cohesive team. We pride ourselves on delivering high quality, evidence-based individualised care. We work closely with carers and community services to support service users during their admission and on discharge back in to the community.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The role will involve co-ordinating shifts, attending ward rounds/ CPA’s, completing medication rounds, key working service users and being part of an excellent and enthusiastic multidisciplinary team, with a vast range of O/T activities on and off the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There are lots of learning opportunities to develop new skills in physical health care and a great experience to work with an interesting service user group. The are also options to take on lead roles within the team and supervision and development of junior staff.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you would like to discuss the role further or arrange a visit to the ward please do contact either myself or one of the Charge Nurses on the ward.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hanna Paddock, Matron - 0117 9195630&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Aspen Ward Charge Nurses- 0117 9195852&lt;/p&gt;
